Japan’s Sendai Shiogama Port Reopens After Tsunami

-- B y   M a s u m i   S u g a   a n d   K i y o t a k a   M a t s u d a
-- 
2011-03-16T08:02:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-16/japan-s-sendai-shiogama-port-reopens-after-tsunami-correct-.html
(Corrects headline, first paragraph to show port
reopened today.)    Japan ’s Sendai Shiogama port
north of  Tokyo  reopened today along with Miyako and Kamaishi
harbors after a magnitude 9 earthquake and tsunami on March
11 caused them to close.  The port in Onahama is also open for emergency uses,
Akiyasu Kurishima, director of administration at the
industries and economy ministry, told reporters today in
Tokyo.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Masumi Suga in Tokyo at 
